  "text": "ROI samples from the first and second ways (vector maps and soil sampling) were used to find rubber plantations established before 2007, while the third way (visual interpretation) was used to find rubber plantations established during 2007 and 2011. Rubber plantations established during 2012 and 2015 were seedlings, which cannot be mapped accurately by either optical and SAR imagery due to complex understory conditions and, therefore, were excluded. The vector maps from the first source was updated using the 2015 rubber plantation map, but only 10% of them were randomly selected as they were spatially clustered. Finally, we obtained 522 ROI samples with establishment year information. The spatial distribution of these ROI samples was presented in Figure 1b and plantation statistics by year was presented in Figure S2 . The clustered ROIs in Figure 1b were selected from the vector maps. The spatial distribution of field data was relatively consistent with the spatial distribution of rubber plantations on Hainan Island [CITATION_1] . We randomly selected five rubber plantations that were established in 1990, 1995, 2000, 2005 , and 2010 from the 522 ROI samples for algorithm training, and the rest were used for validation.",
